        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 3 at 4:38PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 437 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles north of Mt Pleasant, or 10 miles east of Collierville, moving
east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Somerville, Lagrange, Macon, Piperton, Rossville, Moscow, Williston,
Grand Junction, La Grange, Elba, Hays Crossing, Pattersonville, Forty
Five, and Ghost River State Natural Area.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
